title: PPPP Candidate Amjad Khan Afridi wins PK-90 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Pakistan Parliamentarians (PPPP) Amjad Khan Afridi won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-90 Kohat-I by securing 33,785 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ullema Islam Pakistan (JUIP) candidate Muhammad Shoaib who bagged 11,918 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turnout remained 38.6 per cent.
